    Copyright (c) 2014 Delft University of Technology, Jaffalaan 5, 2628 BX Delft, the Netherlands. All rights reserved. The MEDLABS project (Modeling Epidemic Disease with Large-scale Agent-Based Simulation) is aimed at providing policy analysis tools to predict and help contain the spread of epidemics. It makes use of the DSOL simulation engine and the agent-based modeling formalism. See for project information www.simulation.tudelft.nl. The project is a co-operation between TU Delft, Systems Engineering and Simulation Department (Netherlands) and NUDT, Simulation Engineering Department (China).
